# Phase 7A — Vercel upload allowlist.
#
# `.vercelignore` controls what gets uploaded into the Vercel build
# context. Runtime bundles and node_modules are rebuilt fresh on
# Vercel from package.json + pnpm-lock.yaml, so anything listed here
# is excluded purely to keep upload size sane and to stop internal
# documentation + historical git artifacts from bloating the
# deploy image. None of these files are needed at runtime.

# ---- port-workflow git bundles ----------------------------------
# The Flutter→Next port workflow tags every sprint and writes a
# `.bundle` file at repo root as an offline checkpoint. These are
# tracked in history but have zero runtime purpose; excluding them
# trims ~40 MB from every Vercel upload. The tracked copies are left
# in git (removing them is a separate operator decision).
*.bundle

# ---- historical tsconfig buildinfo backups ----------------------
# `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo.old*` are point-in-time backups of TypeScript's
# incremental build cache taken during the port. They are not read
# by `tsc` and not referenced anywhere in the build.
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo.old*

# ---- sandbox tsconfig -------------------------------------------
# Local FUSE-mount workaround that remaps `@/generated/prisma` to a
# sandbox-generated Prisma client. Vercel generates its own client
# during `postinstall`, so this file is irrelevant and should not
# leak into the build context.
tsconfig.sandbox.json

# ---- internal port documentation --------------------------------
# These docs are operator-facing and port-workflow specific. They
# contain change history and internal notes that do not need to ship
# with the running app. README.md, SETUP.md, DEPLOY.md, and
# MIGRATION_BASELINE.md are NOT excluded — they are the operator
# runbooks a fresh clone needs.
PORT_CHECKLIST.md
GIT_WORKFLOW.md

# ---- local .env files -------------------------------------------
# Defense in depth: `.env*` is already in `.gitignore`, but if a
# `.env.local` slips into the workspace it must never be uploaded.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
